---
const title = "Start Here — djerhy.tech";
const description = "Short exercises that reveal gaps between visibility and operational control.";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{title}</title>
  <meta name="description" content={description}>
  
  <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg">
  
  <style>
    * {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
      background: #0D1117;
      color: #e6edf3;
      line-height: 1.6;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 680px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 40px 20px;
    }

    header {
      margin-bottom: 60px;
      padding-bottom: 20px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(230, 237, 243, 0.1);
    }

    .logo {
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #e6edf3;
      text-decoration: none;
      letter-spacing: 0.3px;
    }

    nav {
      display: flex;
      gap: 24px;
      margin-top: 16px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    nav a {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #8b949e;
      text-decoration: none;
      transition: color 0.2s;
    }

    nav a:hover {
      color: #e6edf3;
    }

    h1 {
      font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 44px);
      line-height: 1.1;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    }

    .intro {
      font-size: 16px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #8b949e;
      margin-bottom: 48px;
      max-width: 560px;
    }

    .checks {
      margin-bottom: 60px;
    }

    .check-card {
      background: rgba(230, 237, 243, 0.03);
      border: 1px solid rgba(230, 237, 243, 0.08);
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 24px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
      transition: border-color 0.2s;
    }

    .check-card:hover {
      border-color: rgba(230, 237, 243, 0.15);
    }

    .check-title {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: #e6edf3;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .check-body {
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #8b949e;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .check-result {
      font-size: 14px;
      padding-top: 12px;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(230, 237, 243, 0.08);
    }

    .check-result strong {
      color: #ef4444;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .bridge {
      font-size: 15px;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #8b949e;
      font-style: italic;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 32px;
      padding: 24px;
      background: rgba(230, 237, 243, 0.02);
      border: 1px solid rgba(230, 237, 243, 0.06);
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    .cta {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 60px;
    }

    .cta-primary {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #2F81F7;
      color: white;
      padding: 16px 32px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 16px;
      transition: background 0.2s;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .cta-primary:hover {
      background: #1E6AD8;
    }

    .cta-secondary {
      display: block;
      color: #6e7681;
      font-size: 13px;
      text-decoration: none;
      margin-top: 16px;
    }

    .cta-secondary:hover {
      color: #8b949e;
    }

    footer {
      padding-top: 40px;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(230, 237, 243, 0.1);
      font-size: 13px;
      color: #6e7681;
    }

    .footer-identity {
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .footer-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 16px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    footer a {
      color: #8b949e;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    footer a:hover {
      color: #e6edf3;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      .container {
        padding: 32px 16px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 28px;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <a href="/" class="logo">djerhy.tech</a>
      <nav>
        <a href="/start-here">Start Here</a>
        <a href="/resources">Field Notes</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <h1>Start Here</h1>

      <p class="intro">
        Before running the checks, understand what they are measuring.<br><br>

        Address The Mess is not a troubleshooting guide.<br>
        It evaluates whether an organization can identify responsibility, make decisions, and act on its systems without delay.<br><br>

        The exercises below are signals.<br>
        They do not detect technical flaws.<br>
        They reveal gaps between visibility and operational control.
      </p>

      <section class="checks">
        <div class="check-card">
          <div class="check-title">Check #1: Departed Access</div>
          <div class="check-body">
            Pull a list of people who left in the last 12 months.<br>
            Pick one.<br>
            Check if their access still works.
          </div>
          <div class="check-result">
            Works = <strong>process failure</strong><br>
            Can't check = <strong>visibility failure</strong>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="check-card">
          <div class="check-title">Check #2: Retired Systems</div>
          <div class="check-body">
            Name one system you retired in the last 6 months.<br>
            Check: Network route • Login access • Billing line
          </div>
          <div class="check-result">
            If any answer is "Yes" (or no one can prove "No")<br>
            it's a <strong>Zombie</strong>.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="check-card">
          <div class="check-title">Check #3: Ownership Test</div>
          <div class="check-body">
            Pick your most critical production asset.<br>
            Ask the listed owner:<br>
            <em>"Can you approve taking this offline for 10 minutes right now?"</em>
          </div>
          <div class="check-result">
            If approval isn't immediate,<br>
            the asset is <strong>unowned</strong>.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="check-card">
          <div class="check-title">Check #4: Test/Dev Cleanup</div>
          <div class="check-body">
            Search for assets labeled:<br>
            test / temp / dev / sandbox<br>
            Filter for Publicly Facing.<br>
            Pick one.
          </div>
          <div class="check-result">
            Delete it, or set an expiration date.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="check-card">
          <div class="check-title">Check #5: Asset Drift</div>
          <div class="check-body">
            Count production assets today.<br>
            Find the count from 3 months ago.<br>
            If you can't explain the growth
          </div>
          <div class="check-result">
            you have <strong>Asset Drift</strong>.
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="bridge">
        If even one of these checks felt uncomfortable, the framework shows how to surface and fix this systematically.
      </div>

      <section class="cta">
        <a href="https://2279442040293.gumroad.com/l/srxnun" class="cta-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
          Get the Address The Mess Framework
        </a>
        <a href="/resources" class="cta-secondary">
          → See all field notes
        </a>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <div class="footer-identity">
        Djerhy Jn Baptiste • CISSP
      </div>
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/djerhyjnbaptiste" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
        <a href="https://x.com/JBDjerhy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">X</a>
        <a href="https://www.credly.com/users/djerhy-jn-baptiste" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Credly</a>
      </div>
      <div>© 2026 djerhy.tech</div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
